{
  "doc_id": "48551",
  "text": "Since the OmpR gene reported earlier contained 5'-and 3'-flanking sequences, including the signal sequence [CITATION_1] , cloning of the gene region encoding the mature OmpR in expression vector was carried out. PCR amplification of the OmpR encoding the mature OmpR resulted in amplification of ~0.7 kb DNA fragment of the expected size. Successful cloning of the PCR amplified fragment after digestion with XhoI and KpnI in pRSETA resulted in in frame cloning, confirmed by DNA sequencing. The ompR gene with a single open reading frame would encode an N-terminal 6 × -Histidine tagged recombinant OmpR of ~29.5 kDa, including the amino acid residues contributed by the vector.",
